        <headline>Flood Advisory issued June 13 at 3:32PM EDT until June 13 at 5:45PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.

* WHERE...A portion of central North Carolina, including the
following counties, Montgomery and Stanly.

* WHEN...Until 545 PM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 331 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to
thunderstorms continuing to move northeast over the area.
Additional rain could cause minor or additional flooding.
- Additional rainfall amounts up to 2 inches are expected over
the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Albemarle, Troy, Badin Lake, Biscoe, Norwood, Badin, Mount
Gilead, Star, Candor, Morrow Mountain State Park, Lake
Tillery, Uwharrie Haven, Eldorado, Pekin and Steeds.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
